=farvel>Farvel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/02 6:55:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23103.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Writing notes...</span><hr size=1> Wouldn't it be neat if you could write a note in eq, using a pen and parchment, and hand the note to people? I could see loads of uses on both pvp and non-pvp servers. For one thing, you could jot down notes for further reference. Also, you could make Wanted: posters and leave them on unsuspecting mobs, if you really wanted a PVP player killed. From a RP perspective it would be neat as well. You and your fellow RP'ers could stage newbie quests ala &quot;Take this note to soandso in EC,and he will reward you&quot;. Besides, I want to kill an orc pawn someday and find a &quot;Kilroy was here&quot; note on him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Farvel MacDermott<br>Dark Elf Rogue of the 22nd season<br>E'ci<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulilaradestra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilara d Estra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 11:13:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23103.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org/images/KTF_medium.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing notes...</span><hr size=1> While I think this idea really is neat, I think the reasoning behind it not being in game would be storage of the text on those notes. EQ has over 400,000 subscriptions. The data storage for every single note someone could write would get rather large over time.<br><br>Maybe a more realisitic approach would be making the note linked to your online status. Once you log off, your note poofs. You could also restrict it to One note per person in game at a time.<br><br>Running newbie quests, writing in foreign tongues! Lots of RP aspects to this that would be very neat if it's deemed practical by Verant =) <p><center><b><a href=http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Ibby>Ibby Bay</a><br><b><a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org>Keepers of the Faith</a><br><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88243 >Magelo Bandwagon</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unumruk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numruk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.student.nada.kth.se/~md96-jma/eq/canada.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 12:23:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23103.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/palad/smallskel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing notes...</span><hr size=1> I think the way it works now is, they need to add an entirely new item to the item database every time they add a book or tome to the game. Then they link that item to a text file on the server which opens up when you read the book.<br><br>I don't think it's feasable with the system they have now.<br><br>That said, they should scrap EQ2 (since it would be in direct competition with EQ) and just give EQ a complete overhaul with the PoP expansion. <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81496">Dolalin</a> Bonewielder